<p>TAFISA is excited to announce World Challenge Day 2010 to be held on 26th 
May. We are proud to have 43 participating communities from nearly 40 countries 
to be included. The participating countries are from all over the world so that 
we will have a worldwide competition. The smallest participating city is 
Morotsuka in Japan with a population of 2038, and the biggest city is Tehran in 
Iran with a population of 8.429.800. </p>
<p>New this year is the World Challenge Day Cup where TAFISA will announce 
Regional and Global Winners of World Challenge Day! Thus, the country that is 
capable to motivate more people to be physical active is the winner of the 
friendly international competition in sport for all. We are looking forward to 
the World Challenge Day! Â </p>